{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Lightly grease a large bowl and set aside.","Place a small bowl on top of mixing bowl lid and weigh in butter. Set aside.","Place milk and yeast into mixing bowl and warm <nobr>2 min\/100°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add flour, eggs, sugar and salt and knead <nobr>4 min\/<\/nobr> while adding reserved butter slowly through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Transfer dough into greased bowl and shape into a smooth ball. Cover with cling wrap and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 45 min.)."]},{"title":"Chocolate Filling","content":["Place milk, half and half, eggs, 1 egg yolk, sugar, cocoa powder and flour into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>7 min\/200°F\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and cover with cling wrap touching the surface of the filling and chill, approximately 10 minutes.","Transfer dough onto a lightly floured surface and gently flatten with floured hands to form a rectangle. Roll dough into a rectangle (19.5 in. x 12 in.) with a rolling pin. Spread reserved chocolate filling evenly over the entire surface of the dough (see Tip). Roll dough into a long log. Cut 12 slices (approx 1.5 in.). Transfer slices to a baking sheet lined with parchment. Cover with cling wrap and let rise in a warm place until almost doubled in size (approx. 45 min.).","During the last 15 minutes of the dough rising, preheat oven to 400°F.","Brush buns with remaining egg yolk and sprinkle with pearl sugar. Bake for 20 minutes (400°F) or until dark golden brown. Allow to cool before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["4 oz unsalted butter, softened, cut into pieces, plus extra to grease","7 oz whole milk","1 tbsp active dry yeast","17 ½ oz bread flour","2 large eggs","2 oz sugar","½ tsp salt"]},{"title":"Chocolate Filling","content":["6 ½ oz whole milk","6 oz half and half","2 large eggs","2 egg yolks, from large eggs, divided","2 oz sugar","1 oz unsweetened cocoa powder","½ oz bread flour, plus extra to dust","2 oz pearl sugar, to sprinkle"]}],"id":"r174136","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-5zbYRwBdrdc\/XZanLq2jGGI\/AAAAAAAAg7Y\/QCwtgkEws-40CTpYDG4TOcGE7zCJcpJcwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_56JDJUbUvXcVc7PI.png","title":"Chocolate Swirl Buns","publishedAt":"2017-05-26T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.5 g","fat":"10.3 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"40.3 g","calories":"1205 kJ \/ 285 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling wrap, rolling pin, baking sheet lined with parchment paper, pastry brush, large bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["For easier handling, chill the rolled out dough after you spread chocolate filling for approx. 15-20 minutes before rolling and slicing."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","2h 40m","12 pieces"]}